Quote:  <i>Bush fashion</i>. [page heading] ... He [the Northland sawmiller] wore what is called a `blue shirt', that is, a sailor's shirt of serge, fitting very closely, and a pair of moleskin trousers, very much torn ... from walking through harsh fern and `tea-tree' scrub, ... and a wideawake hat ...
