Edition:
Quote:  <i>Bluey</i> ... (1) A blue blanket ... -->(2) In the wet wildernesses of Western Tasmania a rough shirt or blouse is made of this material, and is worn over the coat like an English smock-frock. Sailors and fishermen in England call it a `Baltic shirt.'
